@node "System" "Requirements"

  To use DMS2HD you need at least an Amiga with harddisk and OS2.04+

  IMPORTANT: The main executable DMS must be installed in C:
             DMS2HD tries to allocate C:DMS. 

  Additionally you must have the workbench installed on your harddisk.

  Optionally DMS2HD will require xadmaster.library by Dirk St÷cker
  in libs:. You can get this powerful unarchiving library from Aminet
  (util/arc/xadmaster.library)

@endnode

@node "ques" "Decrunching a DMS archive"

  Decrunching is simple you can use...

  1) the inbuild MUI GUI: Start DMS2HD. Now you can select a DMS archive,
                          the destination path and some other things.
                          Click the 'Decrunch' button to start the
                          operation!

                          You can set in the menu Settings/DMS2HD which
                          unarchiver DMS2HD shall use. Possible archives
                          are DMS and xadmaster.library. I suggest to use
                          xadmaster as this way is cleaner!

  2) the CLI: This way is good for using DMS2HD with a directory manager.
	      You can then decrunch the files easily with the manager.
	      Especially cool with DirOpus :) OK, there`re two parameters,
	      which need to be specified: DMS2HD archive.dms destination
	      Archive is the DMS archive to decrunch (don`t forget suffix .DMS)
   	      Destination is the path, where to decrunch the files to
	      Here`s an example: DMS2HD Wonderland.dms dh0:Games/Wonderland

              Additionally you can use as the third parameter XADMASTER
              or DMS. This tells DMS2HD which way to use to unpack the archive.
              e.g. 'DMS2HD archive.dms dh4:Files XADMASTER' would use xadmaster.library
              to unpack the archive. Specifying DMS as argument is not really
              necessary as its the default. I suggest to use XADMASTER argument
              for unpacking because this is the cleaner way.

 That was it! If you`ve questions, don`t hesitate to ask @{"me" link "autor"}.
 
@endnode

@node "history" "History"

  V1.6: (Cardware Release Version)

  - fixed some bugs (reported by Uwe Pannecke)
  - some minor changes
  - added a french catalog by Lionel
  - updated doc


  V1.5: (Cardware Release Version)

  - added support for xadmaster.library 
  - fixed a bug
  - added finnish catalog by Samppa R÷nkõ   
  - updated doc and german catalogs
 

  V1.4: (Cardware Release Version)

  - added german catalog + developer files
  - added locale.library support
  - it uses now my own copy routine instead of C:Copy
  - it doesn`t need assigns any more
  - improved decrunching routines
  - improved user-interface
  - improved errorhandle -> no more crashes
  - added MUI GUI


  V1.1: (Freeware Release Version)

  - now freeware: nothing is disabled!!
  - keyfile code removed
  - bug fixes


  V1.0: (Shareware Release Version)

  - simple GUI added
  - better decrunching
  - less bugs (many were fixed)
  - keyfile support
  - Amiga Guide« Documentation


  V0.1: (for private use only)
 
  - very buggy
  - CLI control


  Future plans:

  Not much...unless you`ve some nice ideas. Contact @{"me" link "autor"}
  then.

@endnode

